STATE of North Carolina
v.
Jason Christopher WALKER and Emil E. Browning, Jr. and Javier A. Hernandez Jr. No. 16P05. Supreme Court of North Carolina. May 4, 2005. Brian Michael Aus, Durham, for Emil E. Browning, Jr. Kristine L. Lanning, Assistant Attorney General, Mitchell D. Norton, District Attorney, for State of NC.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the notice of appeal from the North Carolina Court of Appeals, filed by Defendant (Emil E. Browning, Jr.) on the 10th day of January 2005 in this matter pursuant to G.S. 7A-30 (substantial constitutional question), the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the North Carolina Court of Appeals: the notice of appeal is

"Dismissed ex mero motu by order of the Court in conference, this the 4th day of May 2005."

Upon consideration of the petition filed on the 10th day of January 2005 by Defendant (Emil E. Browning, Jr.) in this matter for discretionary review of the decision of the North Carolina Court of Appeals pursuant to G.S. 7A-31, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the North Carolina Court of Appeals:

"Denied by order of the Court in conference, this the 4th day of May 2005."
